{
  "stem": "27748.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So in open competition, I tend to not take part.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But when it comes to, say, solving a puzzle, well, I might not enter into the fray with others trying to solve the puzzle.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But when everybody has given up on it, then I'll go and see whether I can't solve it on my own.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I have this outlook that one can do unusual things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it tends to be independent thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But that, also, I've learned the hard way, is a high risk thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Most people-- like the Salvarsan 606, most people fail who are so independent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, well, we were very much aware of the bombing-- of course, bombing of London, and bombing of the cities in England.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were very conscious of those.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were also aware of the bombings in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I remember now being very pleased about the firebombings of Dresden, where something like 100,000 people were killed in one night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was all gun ho that, yes, yes, this is great stuff that we must do, which now, from my perspective now, I see very differently.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, I don't want to give the sense that I didn't want us to win the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the idea of killing 100,000 people, just flattening out the whole population of a city, or the atomic bombings, or the bombings in-- of English cities by the Germans, now I think of very differently, as being gruesome things that we human beings do to each other.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But to answer your question, I did-- politically, I kept quite closely up with what was happening, the various campaigns and so on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was very much involved in that through newspapers, through reading.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
